  <Docs>
    <summary>Describes a single axis in a variable font's variation design space.</summary>
    <remarks>
      <format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontVariationAxis` holds the metadata for a variable font axis, including its four-character tag identifier, minimum value, default value, maximum value, and visibility flag. Retrieve variation axes using <xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.VariationDesignParameters>.

## Examples

```csharp
var axes = typeface.VariationDesignParameters;
foreach (var axis in axes)
{
    Console.WriteLine($"{axis.Tag}: {axis.Min}..{axis.Default}..{axis.Max}");
}
```
]]></format>
    </remarks>
  </Docs>
